  "instructions": [
    "Saute the chopped onion in a splash of oil in the pressure cooker until soft and fragrant.",
    "Add minced garlic and ginger, cook for 30 seconds until aromatic.",
    "Stir in ground poppy seeds and toast for one minute to release flavor.",
    "Pour in fermented soy sauce, tamari, lemon juice, and water, then mix well.",
    "Add chickpeas and diced tomatoes, stir to combine.",
    "Secure the pressure cooker lid and set to high pressure for 5 minutes.",
    "Release pressure naturally for 5 minutes, then perform a quick release to finish the cycle.",
    "Stir in fresh spinach and black pepper, allowing it to wilt for another minute.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning if needed, then transfer the stew to a serving bowl.",
    "Serve warm over cooked quinoa or rice for a post-workout meal."
  ],
